South Africans are reeling from the gruesome murder of 28-year-old Tshegofatso Pule. She was found murdered and hanging from a tree. Pule had a stab wound to her chest and was eight months pregnant. She will be laid to rest today. The Commission for the Gender Equality's Tamara Mathebula joins us to discuss this senseless killing. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's femicide crisis is once again in the headlines following the gruesome murder of two women. 28-year-old Tshegofatso Pule was stabbed and found hanging from a tree in Johannesburg. She was eight months pregnant at the time of her death. READ: Tshegofatso Pule to be laid to rest on Thursday Her funeral will be held on Thursday. Meanwhile, the family of a Mossel Bay mother is calling for justice. Naledi Phangindawo was hacked to death while attending a cultural festival. The man arrested in connection with her death is the father of two of her three children.